    "## Model Training\n",
    "\n",
    "I used a gated 1D convolutional architecture inspired by [XPixel](https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Pixel-Team-the-network-architecture_fig4_344262557) (for super-resolution tasks), but made a few tweaks.\n",
    "\n",
    "I also tried using Fourier transformations to process inputs in the frequence space using dense networks (frequency domain multiplication = time domain convolution) but it didnt have a great impact, so I removed it. That code can be found at the bottom on the notebook if one is interested\n",
    "\n",
    "I found solid performance when using 128 channels and 16 Self-Calibrated Pixel Attention Blocks"
   ]
  },
